<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="29">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="29">
The epithet 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Pilidiophora" family="Lineidae" genus="Acari" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acari acarorum" order="Heteronemertea" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" phylum="Nemertea" rank="species" species="acarorum">acarorum</taxonomicName>
refers to the subclass 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Pilidiophora" family="Lineidae" genus="Acari" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acari" order="Heteronemertea" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subclass" subclass="Acari">Acari</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Arachnida" family="Lineidae" genus="Acari" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Acari" order="Heteronemertea" pageId="10" pageNumber="29" phylum="Nemertea" rank="class">Arachnida</taxonomicName>
to which all mite species belong from which 25 of the 29 isolates of this species were isolated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="29">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="29">
Sexual state not observed. Hyalorhinocladiella-like asexual state: conidiophores (7-) 18-76.5 (-140) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long; cells arising directly from the hyphae, (10.5-) 13.5-24.5 (-31) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(1-) 1.5-2 (-2) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
; conidia hyaline, smooth, oblong, (3-) 3.5-5 (-6.5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(0.7-) 1-1.5 (-2.5) 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
